[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering Git commands**\n\nI’m looking at scenarios with Git commands involving branches. If the remote info branches are greater than zero, and I create a pull command, it may not work if the source branch is main instead of master. I could initialize a repository with “git init” and even switch branches using “git checkout -b master.” There are concerns about pulling from a checked-out branch which might cause errors. I need to figure out how to properly handle fetching in these cases.\n\n**Analyzing Git behavior**\n\nI'm looking at some existing code that's behaving oddly. I can pull with a null version using `<url> master`, but there's this default branch issue I need to think through. It seems like I could create a master branch and call the version null to avoid complications. Also, initializing a repository with `git init` might not matter if I switch branches right after using `checkout -b master`. I really need to clarify how these commands interact!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_09910bced12b3901016a01e9864960819e95a9297520051242\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqAemRa7T2Z0Ude3vbTDrLAMakkzFDUJoCJaqIsHlUXnuPk_3nd7rON7WVZUl1txGvoZEdm7H8Xl-15v0GnsaFC7US4E0RMYa4JozNF53-e5io_FMGuAuIcj9o1xph7Dxdyd2Ra6QEV2f0owiZNEG32KsnIRJfCHmGMJdpRfg6yHrKWNSvYQxF9iSAdT4C7ulZxuMOfYh83C-HHa0wDol1DBMsLy8eDT3ffz-ZFafQYvrGTPj-64D4Wz8ruHLRkUnA7W2OBHqOA38Z1M9o3l-y0WtRK8C5WEtc1C2eMPazSqrs-JGDskJ8xOegssCRQArLxUL9x7bQTVPwsDgiHUS_k3pQPLRzXjSBIP2M5OMy7WRe9DZv0UMUl_4LUwZt4iNGZhew1SNEElGr_b6YguDTTgPN_1nZ1QdPBiLEB7-bwmgBZD66gTgRI--UeDCMwgTd69h8mj7moJ7nsKcjgr3xBNwuV09-R5_vAsP_QOtRmf5mv52Fe3c8Sik3m5IHbDWjggizo_gMnm8BhoAqKFR96Gde6IjH97JLv-tmgNoU-9Ufj9Qo85TmewQ4auG4z8rxe7WZBCZRqBcTu8SznEcoPuv1tpuONYwpxf-qxfwUt146RiY7QNlyNER7xI6OUKbr6kPwyOhmr4tngDelUU8UPhx9LqZ5P4ZUAbv1pXj44SaGPYnRUiVIGpzDgsTOr_D_NaQ8L-J_pvp8PEq4LeSGXGS9z5Gp1tayJgMLW3_oyzNkS8ZYC8vTQUsiMkQqqQ